a=0;b=1
S_m=function(h)
{
g=seq(a,b,h)
g1=(g+h/2)[-length(g)]
S=h*(sum(sin(g1)))
err=abs(S-(cos(a)-cos(b)))
return(c(S,err))
}
S_t=function(h)
{
g=seq(a,b,h)
S=h*(sum(sin(g))-(sin(a)+sin(b))/2)
err=abs(S-(cos(a)-cos(b)))
return(c(S,err))
}

  1. Approximation of \(\pi\)

\[\int_0^1 \sqrt{1-x^2} dx = \arcsin (1)/2 = \pi/4\]

S_pi=function(h)
{
g=seq(a,b,h)
S=h*(sum(sqrt(1-g^2))-(sqrt(1-a^2)+sqrt(1-b^2))/2)
err=abs(S-(pi/4))
return(c(4*S,4*err))
}

3.2 Metropolis-Hastings algorithm

. proposal \(q(\cdot|\cdot)\) , .

  • step 1 () \(X_0\) .
  • step 2 proposal distribution \(y\) . \[y\sim q(y|x_t),~t=1,2,\ldots\]
  • step 3 acceptance probability . \[\alpha(y|x_t)=\min\left\{1,\frac{\pi(y)q(x_t|y)}{\pi(x_t)q(y|x_t)} \right\}\]
  • step 4 \(U\sim U(0,1)\) .
  • step 5 \(U\leq \alpha(y|x_t)\) \(x_t=y_t\), \(U > \alpha(y|x_t)\) \(x_t=x_{t-1}\)

(\(m\)) \(X_1,\ldots,X_m\) \(\pi\) . normalizing constant . , .

  • Example 1

\[\pi(x)=10^xe^{-1}/x!\]

proposal

\[q(y|x)=0.5I(|y-x|=1)\]

, acceptance probability

\[y=x-1~;~\alpha(x-1|x)=\min(1,x/10)\] \[y=x+1~;~\alpha(x+1|x)=\min(1,10/(x+1))\]

.

x0=10;x<-x0
set.seed(1)
N=3000
for (i in 1:N)
  {
  y=sample(c(x[i]-1,x[i]+1),1)
  alpha=min(1,x[i]/10)*(y==x[i]-1)+min(1,10/(x[i]+1))*(y==x[i]+1)
  U=runif(1)
  x[i+1]=y*(U<alpha)+x[i]*(U>alpha)
  }
plot(x[1:200],type="l")

hist(x[-1])

mean(x[-1]);var(x[-1])

proposal \(q(y|X)=q(y)\) . , proposal iid . proposal .

\[\pi(x) \propto \exp(-n(x-0.05)^2/2)\times 1/(1+x^2)\]

x0=0.05;x<-x0;n=20
set.seed(1)
N=3000
pis=function(x){exp(-n*(x-0.0675)^2/2)/(1+x^2)}
for (i in 1:N)
  {
  y=rcauchy(1)
  alpha=min(1,(pis(y)*dcauchy(x[i]))/(pis(x[i])*dcauchy(y)))
  U=runif(1)
  x[i+1]=y*(U<alpha)+x[i]*(U>alpha)
  }
plot(x[1:200],type="l")

mean(x[500:3000]);var(x[500:3000]) # posterior mean & variance
